            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EHow%20important%20it%20is%20to%20have%20your%20own%20knowledge%20of%20the%20Word%20of%20God!%20What%20your%20parents%20or%20grandparents%20knew%20and%20taught%20you%20about%20the%20Word%20of%20God%20should%20not%20be%20your%20only%20source%20of%20revelation.%20Your%20own%20eyes%20must%20see%20God's%20Word%2C%20and%20then%20you%20must%20hide%20it%20inside%20your%20heart.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIf%20Solomon%20had%20obeyed%20Moses'%20command%20to%20produce%20a%20handwritten%20copy%20of%20the%20law%20(Deuteronomy%2017%3A14-20)%2C%20he%20would%20have%20known%20for%20himself%20some%20important%20things.%20For%20example%2C%20he%20would%20have%20known%20not%20to%20acquire%20horses%20from%20Egypt%2C%20take%20multiple%20wives%2C%20or%20accumulate%20large%20amounts%20of%20silver%20and%20gold%20(vv.%2016-17).%20Obedience%20to%20these%20three%20simple%20commands%20would%20have%20kept%20him%20from%20all%20his%20troubles.%20In%20fact%2C%20however%2C%20these%20were%20the%20very%20sins%20he%20committed%20(1%20Kings%2010%3A26-11%3A13).%20What%20a%20tragedy!%20If%20only%20Solomon%20had%20hidden%20God's%20Word%20in%20his%20heart%2C%20he%20might%20not%20have%20sinned%20against%20God%20(Psalm%20119%3A11).%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EYour%20own%20personal%2C%20diligent%2C%20daily%20study%20of%20the%20Word%20will%20undoubtedly%20protect%20you%20from%20much%20deception%20and%20heartache.%20Moses%20passed%20down%20suitable%20guidelines%20for%20a%20king%2C%20instructing%20that%20he%20read%20them%20daily%20throughout%20his%20life.%20In%20the%20same%20way%2C%20if%20you%20read%20God's%20Word%20every%20day%20and%20hide%20its%20truths%20in%20your%20heart%2C%20you%20will%20be%20equipped%20to%20live%20it.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Deuteronomy.16:1-17:20",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EDeuteronomy%2016%3A1-17%3A20%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_1%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EDeuteronomy%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EPassover%20and%20the%20Festival%20of%20Unleavened%20Bread%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BIn%20honor%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%2C%20celebrate%20the%20Passover%20each%20year%20in%20the%20early%20spring%2C%20in%20the%20month%20of%20Abib%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E16%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EObserve%20the%20month%20of%20Abib%2C%20and%20keep%20the%20Passover%20unto%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ci%20class%3D%22tn-sc-ital%22%3ELord%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cem%3E%20your%20God.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Abib%2C%20the%20first%20month%20of%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar%2C%20usually%20occurs%20within%20the%20months%20of%20March%20and%20April.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20for%20that%20was%20the%20month%20in%20which%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20brought%20you%20out%20of%20Egypt%20by%20night.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_2%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EYour%20Passover%20sacrifice%20may%20be%20from%20either%20the%20flock%20or%20the%20herd%2C%20and%20it%20must%20be%20sacrificed%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20at%20the%20designated%20place%20of%20worship%26%23x2014%3Bthe%20place%20he%20chooses%20for%20his%20name%20to%20be%20honored.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_3%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EEat%20it%20with%20bread%20made%20without%20yeast.%20For%20seven%20days%20the%20bread%20you%20eat%20must%20be%20made%20without%20yeast%2C%20as%20when%20you%20escaped%20from%20Egypt%20in%20such%20a%20hurry.%20Eat%20this%20bread%26%23x2014%3Bthe%20bread%20of%20suffering%26%23x2014%3Bso%20that%20as%20long%20as%20you%20live%20you%20will%20remember%20the%20day%20you%20departed%20from%20Egypt.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_4%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3ELet%20no%20yeast%20be%20found%20in%20any%20house%20throughout%20your%20land%20for%20those%20seven%20days.%20And%20when%20you%20sacrifice%20the%20Passover%20lamb%20on%20the%20evening%20of%20the%20first%20day%2C%20do%20not%20let%20any%20of%20the%20meat%20remain%20until%20the%20next%20morning.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_5%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BYou%20may%20not%20sacrifice%20the%20Passover%20in%20just%20any%20of%20the%20towns%20that%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20is%20giving%20you.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_6%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EYou%20must%20offer%20it%20only%20at%20the%20designated%20place%20of%20worship%26%23x2014%3Bthe%20place%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20chooses%20for%20his%20name%20to%20be%20honored.%20Sacrifice%20it%20there%20in%20the%20evening%20as%20the%20sun%20goes%20down%20on%20the%20anniversary%20of%20your%20exodus%20from%20Egypt.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_7%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3ERoast%20the%20lamb%20and%20eat%20it%20in%20the%20place%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20chooses.%20Then%20you%20may%20go%20back%20to%20your%20tents%20the%20next%20morning.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_8%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EFor%20the%20next%20six%20days%20you%20may%20not%20eat%20any%20bread%20made%20with%20yeast.%20On%20the%20seventh%20day%20proclaim%20another%20holy%20day%20in%20honor%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%2C%20and%20no%20work%20may%20be%20done%20on%20that%20day.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_9%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Festival%20of%20Harvest%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BCount%20off%20seven%20weeks%20from%20when%20you%20first%20begin%20to%20cut%20the%20grain%20at%20the%20time%20of%20harvest.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_10%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20celebrate%20the%20Festival%20of%20Harvest%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E16%3A10%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EFestival%20of%20Weeks%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2016%3A16.%20This%20was%20later%20called%20the%20Festival%20of%20Pentecost%20(see%20Acts%202%3A1).%20It%20is%20celebrated%20today%20as%20Shavuot%20(or%20Shabuoth).%3C%2Fspan%3E%20to%20honor%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God.%20Bring%20him%20a%20voluntary%20offering%20in%20proportion%20to%20the%20blessings%20you%20have%20received%20from%20him.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_11%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20a%20time%20to%20celebrate%20before%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20at%20the%20designated%20place%20of%20worship%20he%20will%20choose%20for%20his%20name%20to%20be%20honored.%20Celebrate%20with%20your%20sons%20and%20daughters%2C%20your%20male%20and%20female%20servants%2C%20the%20Levites%20from%20your%20towns%2C%20and%20the%20foreigners%2C%20orphans%2C%20and%20widows%20who%20live%20among%20you.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_12%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3ERemember%20that%20you%20were%20once%20slaves%20in%20Egypt%2C%20so%20be%20careful%20to%20obey%20all%20these%20decrees.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_13%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Festival%20of%20Shelters%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BYou%20must%20observe%20the%20Festival%20of%20Shelters%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E16%3A13%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EFestival%20of%20Booths%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3EFestival%20of%20Tabernacles%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2016%3A16.%20This%20was%20earlier%20called%20the%20Festival%20of%20the%20Final%20Harvest%20or%20Festival%20of%20Ingathering%20(see%20Exod%2023%3A16b).%20It%20is%20celebrated%20today%20as%20Sukkot%20(or%20Succoth).%3C%2Fspan%3E%20for%20seven%20days%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20harvest%20season%2C%20after%20the%20grain%20has%20been%20threshed%20and%20the%20grapes%20have%20been%20pressed.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_14%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20festival%20will%20be%20a%20happy%20time%20of%20celebrating%20with%20your%20sons%20and%20daughters%2C%20your%20male%20and%20female%20servants%2C%20and%20the%20Levites%2C%20foreigners%2C%20orphans%2C%20and%20widows%20from%20your%20towns.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_15%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EFor%20seven%20days%20you%20must%20celebrate%20this%20festival%20to%20honor%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20at%20the%20place%20he%20chooses%2C%20for%20it%20is%20he%20who%20blesses%20you%20with%20bountiful%20harvests%20and%20gives%20you%20success%20in%20all%20your%20work.%20This%20festival%20will%20be%20a%20time%20of%20great%20joy%20for%20all.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_16%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BEach%20year%20every%20man%20in%20Israel%20must%20celebrate%20these%20three%20festivals%3A%20the%20Festival%20of%20Unleavened%20Bread%2C%20the%20Festival%20of%20Harvest%2C%20and%20the%20Festival%20of%20Shelters.%20On%20each%20of%20these%20occasions%2C%20all%20men%20must%20appear%20before%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20at%20the%20place%20he%20chooses%2C%20but%20they%20must%20not%20appear%20before%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20without%20a%20gift%20for%20him.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_17%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EAll%20must%20give%20as%20they%20are%20able%2C%20according%20to%20the%20blessings%20given%20to%20them%20by%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_16_18%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subh